That the following article is proposed as an amendment to the 
Constitution of the United States, which shall be valid to all intents and 
purposes as part of the Constitution when ratified by the legislatures of 
three-fourths of the several States: 
“ARTICLE ___
Section 1:
No person may serve as a federal, appellate or supreme court judge in 
the Article III branch of federal government – the Judiciary – unless that 
person be first recommended in writing by a sitting judge in said branch 
of government, to a sitting President.”
